metadata.name: Sea of Shapes #8
metadata.description:
This program was inspired by the 2022 Genuary prompt "Make a sea of shapes." It is an abstract and geometric representation of water and waves. I tried to capture the many different possible states of a sea (windy, breezy, calm etc.) by changing parameters within the program for different outputs.

Press 'p' while on Live View to save a high quality (4000x4000) png of the canvas.

Created using p5.js

Licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Happy Accidents #75
metadata.description:
Sometimes when you're working on your Creative Coding project, you make a change to the code and it breaks. But maybe that's a good thing. This project was created as a fun expression of what can happen if you allow yourself to go down the rabbit hole, and further break your code until you come up with a new idea.

Special thanks to @clayheaton and @sableRaph for the coding tips and tricks.

metadata.name: Cattails #13
metadata.description:
Enjoy the peaceful solitude of a cool morning in this floral, marshland landscape.  Features include generative cattails, bushes, rocks, moss, mushrooms and flowers in a random palette scheme framed in lush, verdant foliage.

Press DOWN ARROW to save any frame as a png file.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode. 

Created using the p5js library.
Designed and coded by Ed Cavett.
Published April, 25, 2022.
50 ed. @ 2tz each.

metadata.name: Black Forest #2
metadata.description:
Imagine you are walking in the middle of the night towards the mountains, the moon is shining behind you, You hear the night creatures arround you yet you fear none because you know you are strong. 

Fully generative forest done first in processing in Android(in my mobile phone) then passed to p5js. No shaders.

metadata.name: Mediterranean #317
metadata.description:
How diverse can nature be?

Created with p5js.
Code takes a few minutes to complete. Needs a good CPU.
Works faster on Chrome browser.
For high-res images: Type a resolution multiplier number on live view. If you type 2, it will render 2 times larger than your screen size. Press "s" to save.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #28
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.
